Ancient and medieval Indian cities often emphasized water management, waste disposal, and sanitation, with sophisticated tank and canal systems.


When the British colonized India, their policies prioritized resource extraction and trade advantages for Britain rather than the welfare of local populations. Infrastructure was often designed to serve British administrative and commercial interests (like railways for moving raw materials), not local health or sanitation. By the time they left in 1947, much of the subcontinentâ€™s economy and infrastructure had been reoriented around colonial needs â€” and many indigenous systems of civic management and education had deteriorated or been replaced.

I genuinely, for the love of god, do not understand the mindset of foreigners in india.

Come on, you have such good money advantage as a foreigner! India isn't only crowded and rural! Finally, I'm only saying all this because I'm concerned for you please don't take it in any wrong way.

Water from the Ganges has been linked to dysentery, cholera, hepatitis, and severe diarrhea, which remains one of the leading causes of death among children in India.  But pollution, dams and removal of too much water (mostly for agriculture) have affected the flow and health of this vital river. One of the river's most at-risk animals is the Ganges river dolphin. The Ganga today is facing formidable pollution pressures, along with the attendant threats to its biodiversity and environmental sustainability.

Kashi is a very very old historic city in India. It was originally designed to have consecrated temples to replicate the human energy system(nadis, chakras), so that the city behaves like a living organism to benefit people in their spiritual process.
Explanation for the reason why Hindus burn the dead body along with throwing the ashes in a river - Human body is made of different layers like physical, mental, energetic structures along with the soul(non physical part of our being). When a person dies, physical and mental structure disappears but the soul stays on and tries to find another womb. After death, the energetic structure takes a few days to completely leave the being(that is why you see some processes like fingernails growing even for the dead body). If the dead body is not burned, some occult and black magic people can utilize this energy and cause pain to the being. The ashes can also be misused, so they disperse it in a flowing river.

Hindus worship nature, rivers plants animals.  
For example, one of the reasons why Ganga is worshipped if you look at it from pragmatic point of veiw the river irrigates the massive Gangetic doab region, and makes the soil fertile. Directly or indirectly, 200M people are dependent on its sacred waters for their livelihoods. Without it life would be really difficult in Gangatic planes. 
Hindus worship banyan tree because of it emiting the outsized amount of oxygen.  Hindus worship Basil tree, for its medicinal purposes, or sun for its importance in role for the sustainance of life so on and on.  Its our way of giving thanks to the nature so on and on.
